This paper discusses the problem of abstracting conditional probabilistic actions, which is a topic related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of abstraction in decision-making and planning, which falls under the category of programming languages (cs.PL) and robotics (cs.RO). Finally, the paper discusses the use of abstraction in reducing complexity, which is a topic related to systems and control (cs.SY).
